Options other than [--method] have been proved working well either personally by
me or by users testing ACSwitch. [--method] is perhaps the only one that needs a
little attention of mine, but not forgetting others though.

Another thing to note here is that we do not detect whether charger is connected
before writing to the trigger, which in turn may result in kernel wakelocks that
may take up CPU cycles hitting performance.

Once above is satisfied, I may release the very first completely stable version.
